cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses information theoretical analysis of the proposed framework and its coding gains, making it highly likely to belong to this sub-category. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless networks and data collection, which falls under the purview of this sub-category. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed framework involves real-time adaptation and distributed nature, which are key aspects of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the use of circulant low-density parity-check codes, which are commonly used in multimedia applications. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a distributed coding framework, making it relevant to this sub-category.
